This emacs mode provides a major mode for the song files ".sg"
of the Patacrep Songbook available at: http://www.patacrep.com

To install, put the file songbook.el in ~/.config/emacs/
Make the folder if it does not already exist.

Then, append the following lines in your emacs configuration file ~/.emacs
(make it if it does not exist yet):

(setq load-path (cons "~/.config/emacs" load-path))
(setq auto-mode-alist (cons '("\\.sg$" . songbook-mode) auto-mode-alist))
(setq auto-mode-alist (cons '("\\.sbd$" . songbook-mode) auto-mode-alist))
(autoload 'songbook-mode "songbook" "Major mode for Patacrep's songbooks" t)

Files are hosted as a git project on github: 
http://github.com/crep4ever/songbook-emacs-mode.git

Any remarks or comments may be adressed at romain.goffe@gmail.com
